title: Boise State sports roundup: Tennis player sweeps home tournament titles
text:
Order a reprint of this story 
BOISE — Thomas Tenreiro rallied from a set down to beat Utah State’s Jaime Barajas 6-7 (5), 6-3, 6-2 in the singles final, then he teamed with Abe Hewko to beat Air Force’s Lucas Famagalli and Max Olson 6-3 for the doubles title at the Dar Walters Fall Classic on Sunday at the Appleton Tennis Center. The senior went 6-0 as the top singles seed, and he and Hewko went 5-0 to win as the No. 6 seed in the Broncos’ final home appearance of 2015. 
BSU WOMEN’S SOCCER: The Broncos (3-7-3, 1-3-0 Mountain West) lost to Fresno State 4-1 in Fresno, Calif. Brooke Heidemann (Rocky Mountain High) scored in the second straight game for Boise State, and Tara Fisher had eight saves.
